pending_tasks.description: Create a PostgreSQL schema and seed data that mirrors the mock e-commerce domain (products, categories, users, orders, wishlist, cart) to support realistic browsing/search/account flows.
requirements: Schema supports: hierarchical categories (parent-child), products with categoryPath/sku/descriptions/price/rating/reviewCount/image, users with addresses, orders with line items, wishlist items, and (optional) cart tables
Seed data includes: full category tree matching the required top-level categories, 50+ products distributed across categories, 1 demo user with addresses, 3–5 recent orders, and a non-empty wishlist
Ensure referential integrity and indexes for common queries: category slug lookup, product search fields (name/sku/descriptions), and product-category relationships
Seed data should be deterministic and suitable for UI demos (images can be URLs/placeholders but must be valid strings)
acceptance_criteria: Database container initializes successfully using the init scripts without errors
Schema includes all required entities and relationships (categories hierarchy, products, users, orders, wishlist)
Seed data loads and basic sanity queries return expected counts (e.g., categories present, products present, demo user present, orders present)
No missing foreign keys or broken references in seeded rows

pending_tasks.description: Implement an Express.js API that serves the storefront with mock/demo data (from DB or in-memory) and supports search, category browsing, cart, wishlist, and mock authentication flows.
requirements: Provide /health endpoint returning 200 with service status

Implement endpoints per API contracts: categories tree, category by slug, products listing, product by id, advanced search with filters (name/sku/description/shortDescription/price min/max), and category product listing with sorting/pagination
Implement mock auth: sign-in with any non-empty credentials, session creation (cookie or token), sign-out, and protected account endpoints requiring auth
Implement cart and wishlist endpoints: add/remove/toggle, update quantities, fetch current cart/wishlist; return computed subtotal and item counts
Return consistent error shapes and handle empty results gracefully (e.g., empty arrays, 200 with no results)
CORS and configuration suitable for local Docker + Vite dev
acceptance_criteria: Backend starts and stays running; /health returns 200
All documented endpoints respond with correct status codes and JSON shapes
Advanced search returns correct filtered results for combinations of fields and price range
Auth-protected endpoints reject unauthenticated requests and succeed after sign-in
Cart and wishlist operations persist for the session (and/or user) and return updated counts/subtotals

pending_tasks.description: Build a responsive React + Vite storefront UI matching the classic eBay-style layout and implementing all required navigation and flows end-to-end using the mock backend.
requirements: Global layout on all pages: sticky header with utility links, welcome message when signed in, search bar, cart icon with badge, advanced search link; footer with links and newsletter subscribe demo
Primary category navigation with hover mega-menu (left column subcategories, right column deeper subcategories) and click routing to /category/:slug (or nested paths)
Home page: 8–12 product showcase grid with real data, ProductCard includes image/name/rating+reviewCount/price/Add to Cart/wishlist toggle
Advanced Search page: form fields (name, sku, description, shortDescription, min/max price) and results list with empty state
Login page: two-column layout, show password toggle, sign-in validation (non-empty), sign-out, and account gating/redirects

My Account page: left sidebar nav, main content with user info, default addresses, newsletter status, recent orders table with actions (View Order/Reorder) that perform meaningful demo behaviors (e.g., open modal, navigate to stub detail, or add items to cart)
My Wish List page: empty and populated states; remove and add-to-cart actions
Category page: breadcrumb, title, left filter rail with price ranges + counts, sort dropdown, items count text, product grid, pagination controls; mobile collapsible filters
UX quality: loading states for all fetches, friendly error states, no dead controls (disabled with explanation or implemented), keyboard navigable forms, responsive layout
State management: cart/wishlist/session persisted via localStorage (optional) and synchronized with backend responses

reference_images.purpose: Header/search/category navigation styling and overall storefront layout cues
Product card/grid styling, spacing, and information hierarchy
Category page structure: filter rail, sort bar, results grid, pagination
Account and wishlist page layouts: sidebar navigation, tables/lists, utility links
Advanced search form layout and results presentation

acceptance_criteria: All required routes render and are reachable via navigation (no broken links)
Home shows real product data; Add to Cart and wishlist toggles update UI and cart badge immediately
Category mega-menu opens on hover and routes correctly on click; works on desktop and degrades appropriately on mobile
Advanced Search filters products correctly and shows a clear 'No results found' state
Login creates a mock session; account pages require sign-in and redirect to /login when signed out
My Account displays user info, addresses, newsletter status, and recent orders table with working actions
Wishlist page supports empty and populated states; remove and add-to-cart work
Category page supports filtering, sorting, and pagination with correct item counts
No console errors; no unexpected network 4xx/5xx; loading/error/empty states present across pages

pending_tasks.description: Create an OpenEnv adapter that exposes key user journeys and state for agent interaction (browse/search/add to cart/wishlist/login/account).
requirements: Implement adapter endpoints/actions to: navigate to routes, perform search, add/remove cart items, toggle wishlist, sign in/out, and fetch current session/cart/wishlist summaries
Expose a minimal, stable interface for automated testing (e.g., list categories, list products by category, run advanced search, get account summary)
Ensure adapter can run alongside docker-compose and target the frontend/backend URLs correctly
acceptance_criteria: OpenEnv adapter starts without errors and can reach the running services
Agent actions can complete core flows: browse category → add to cart → view cart summary; toggle wishlist; sign in → view account summary
Adapter returns consistent structured responses suitable for automation

pending_tasks.description: Provide Docker configuration to build and run database, backend, frontend, and env adapter reliably for local development and demo use.
requirements: docker-compose configuration for production-like run (all services) and a dev compose for hot reload where appropriate
Correct networking and environment variables so frontend can call backend and backend can call database
Healthchecks and startup ordering so services come up cleanly
Documented ports and URLs for accessing the app and API
acceptance_criteria: All containers build successfully
docker compose up starts all services and they remain healthy
Backend /health returns 200 from host
Frontend is accessible in browser and can complete core flows against the running backend
No recurring container restarts or crash loops
